The paper deals with the analysis of sparse-graph codes under message-passing decoding, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also introduces new tools for deriving information combining inequalities, which is a topic in coding theory (cs.CC). The use of optimization techniques in the analysis of low-density parity-check codes suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the application of message-passing decoding suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
